headline: Dell earnings, housing data, Fed commentary: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination host Josh Lipton takes a look at the top stories for investors to watch on Thursday, Aug. 28. Dollar General (DG) will report earnings results in the morning. In the afternoon, Dell (DELL), Marvell (MRVL), Affirm (AFRM), Ulta (ULTA), and Gap (GAP) report results. Pending home sales data for July will be out in the morning. Economists expect an annualized decrease of -0.2%. Federal Reserve Governor Christopher Waller will be delivering remarks at 6 p.m. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination.
